(232, '364473', 29, 'Royal Myanmar Academy', 'storage/certificates/logos/67d7d9dfcfcca.download (2).png', 'storage/certificates/images/687255706fcb1.1736244213.png', '<p>This certificate is proudly awarded to Mya Thandar in recognition of her successful completion of the Certificate in Hospitality Management Course. Through dedication and hard work, Mya Thandar has demonstrated proficiency in key hospitality management principles. We commend her commitment to excellence and wish her continued success in her career.</p>', '<p>Course Outlines &bull; &nbsp;Customer Service &bull; &nbsp;Restaurant Services &bull; &nbsp;Fundamentals Of The Hotel &amp; Catering Industry &bull; &nbsp;Housekeeping &amp; Accommodation Studies &bull; &nbsp;Food &amp; Beverage Management &bull; &nbsp;Front Office Operations &amp; Administration &bull; &nbsp;Strategic Management In Hospitality &bull; &nbsp;Organisational Behaviour &amp; Hospitality Management &bull; &nbsp;Environmental Management In The Hospitality Industry Course Objectives: Upon completion of this program, participants will be able to: 1) &nbsp;Deliver Effective Customer Service: Provide high-quality service and resolve customer issues. 2) &nbsp;Manage Restaurant Operations: Execute efficient restaurant service and manage related tasks. 3) &nbsp;Understand Hotel &amp; Catering Fundamentals: Grasp core concepts of the hospitality industry. 4) &nbsp;Apply Housekeeping &amp; Accommodation Standards: Maintain high standards for guest accommodations. 5) &nbsp;Manage Food &amp; Beverage Services: Control costs and optimize food and beverage operations. 6) &nbsp;Administer Front Office Procedures: Handle guest services and front desk tasks. 7) &nbsp;Implement Hospitality Strategic Management: Develop and apply strategic plans. 8) &nbsp;Analyze Hospitality Organizational Behavior: Understand team dynamics and workplace behavior.</p>', NULL, '2025-07-12 12:30:40', '2025-07-12 12:32:13', 1, 'storage/certificates/qrcodes/364473.png', NU